WorldStage Newsonline– Ahead of the forthcoming general elections, Kaduna State Governor, Mallam Nasir El-Rufai of the All Progressive Congress, the Peoples Democratic Party’s governorship candidate, Alhaji Isa Ashiru and other candidates on Tuesday signed a peace accord. The peace accord signed at the Police Headquarters along Bida Road in the state capital was to ensure a conduct of free, fair and credible elections as well as a peaceful transition of political powers in the state. The State Police Commissioner, Ahmad Abdulrahman in his remarks, said the Force would be fair and firm to all political parties in the state before, during and after the elections. He called on all political parties and other relevant stakeholders to partner with the police to ensure a violence- free polls in the state. According to him, a violence-free election is a fundamental means to a sustainable peace and development. The police chief said, “we will be firm and  fair while discharging their duties told the politicians at the gathering that winning election into public office should not be a desperate task. “Peace Accord signifies our respective commitment to peace and symbolizes respect for the rule of law. “I want to suggest that candidates and supporters must accept the outcome as announced by the constituted authorities, rather than make trouble because the results are not in one’s favour. “Let us prepare our minds to accept the results for the sake of our dear nation. While those who will emerge as winners, must not allow themselves and their supporters when jubilating, to tease and provoke the other sides.” The PDP governorship candidate called on INEC to provide a level playing ground to all the political parties during the elections.